FBIS4-46396 "jptot024__l94073" JPRS-TOT-94-024-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 6 June 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA INDIA Arrest of `Militant' Said To Prevent Terrorism Arrest of `Militant' Said To Prevent Terrorism BK0606131794 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 GMT 6 Jun 94 BK0606131794 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] With the arrest of a most wanted Kashmiri militant, Mushtaq Ahmad, and his two associates, the Delhi police has foiled their plans to assassinate prominent leaders and to spread terrorism in metropolitan towns of the country. Giving details, the additional commissioner of police, Mr. R.S. Gupta, told newsmen that preliminary interrogations revealed a conspiracy by Hizbul Mojahedin to spread terrorism by using fundamentalist Muslims.
